snippet: The pilot of the F-16 was able to eject safely, but the occupants of the two-seat Cessna C150 plane died. They were not identified.
abstract: National Transportation Safety Board says two people died after small civilian aircraft crashed midair into F-16 fighter jet near Charleston, SC.
lead_paragraph: The pilot of the F-16 was able to eject safely, but the occupants of the two-seat Cessna C150 plane died. They were not identified.

headline.main: Private Plane and F-16 Jet Collide Over South Carolina; 2 Are Killed
headline.print_headline: Private Plane and F-16 Jet Collide in Air; 2 Are Killed
